casebody.data:
Catherine M. LANE, Petitioner, v. COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE, Respondent. No. 7839. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. April 17, 1935. Guy Chase, of St. Paul, Minn., for petitioner. Frank J. Wideman, Asst. Atty. Gen., and Robert H. Jackson, Asst. Gen. Counsel, Bureau of Internal Revenue, of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon motion of counsel for respondent, consented to by counsel for petitioner, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered petition to review herein dismissed; mandate forthwith.
